classes A, B, C, G, H;

left = strict[(A, 1), (B, 2), (C, 3)];
right = rr[G, H];

return wfq[(left, 1), (right, 3)]

// The present tree is
//            wfq
//          /    \
//         /      \
//     strict      rr
//     / | \       / \
//    A  B  C     G   H
//
// and this is complex_tree:
//              wfq
//           /   |   \
//         /     |     \
//     strict    rr      rr
//     / | \    / | \    / \
//    A  B  C  F  E  D  G   H
//
// Our intention is to compare the present tree to complex_tree, and we expect a report that RR[DEF] was added. The report will say DEF and not FED because it will normalize the tree first.
